      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LADY GUNAI (6) could manage only second at Healesville last time but turned heads when posting a lightning 16.44 over 300m at Healesville three starts ago. Has the ability and looks hard to top. ULTIMO (2) flew the lids with a fast early split last time, hitting the frame with a one length second (22.89) over 400m at this track and making it two placings on end. Deserves a win and gets his chance. RAM RAID (7) was quickly into stride and raced on speed before sticking on for a minor placing third (22.28) at Shepparton in Grade 5. Has been out the placings in all two runs here. Comes through a solid form race last start. Overdue and expected to feature again. FOXY ROXY (1) cannot be ruled out.",
